</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1887,2021]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="261" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">
Anal tube without process. Aedeagal shaft long and slender, with pair of slender apical processes; apodeme bilobed, extended into pair of dorsolateral antlerlike extensions, and crossing aedeagal shaft in lateral view; ventral processes absent (
<figureCitation box="[352,452,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[173,1420,202,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1431,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Riseveinus cervcornutus sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. connective and style, ventral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. aedeagal, lateral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607074/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="261">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
